    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened (you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[550ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
