      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add your<strong> lean</strong> <strong>beef mince</strong> to the pan and cook for a further 5 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Add your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>cumin</strong>, <strong>ras el hanout </strong>and the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>to the pan and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Add the <strong>tomato stock</strong> and cook for 7-8 min or until the sauce has thickened and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
